                            <comment id="12895130" author="ranjit" created="Wed, 4 Aug 2010 03:49:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there no umask set for the corresponding user?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Even if the default permissions are 777, the umask setting should have stripped some of them out upon file-creation.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12895131" author="tlipcon" created="Wed, 4 Aug 2010 04:03:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The umask is set, but create() actually specifically chmods the file to 777 after it&apos;s created.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12910025" author="mishravivek" created="Thu, 16 Sep 2010 06:08:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Solution to this issue is to use: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FsPermission.getUMask(this.getConf()) !=null?FsPermission.getUMask(this.getConf()):FsPermission.getDefault().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please suggest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12979704" author="nidaley" created="Mon, 10 Jan 2011 19:31:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking it as a blocker for now.  Not, however, a regression.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
